Description: Very small scaraboid made of blue frit, completely preserved. The back shows a duck with the neck bent backwards, the feathers of the back are indicated by lines, the legs are shown bent at the side. The side shows an incised line surrounding the object. The seal does notshow an oval framing line, but is incised with small hieroglyphs: the middle shows a mn-n-t-t flanked on both sides with a nb-basket. Very thin perforation along its longitudinal side, not exactly in the centre.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.22, top of west wall, north end
